  "instructions": [
    "Cook the bacon in a large pot over medium heat until crispy, then remove from heat and set aside.",
    "Chop the onion and cook in the pot until softened, about 5 minutes.",
    "Mince the garlic and cook for another minute, until fragrant.",
    "Add the split peas, pork stock, tomato paste, ground mustard, ground cumin, smoked paprika, kosher salt, and black pepper to the pot. Stir to combine.",
    "Bring the stew to a boil, then reduce the heat to low and simmer for 45 minutes, or until the peas are tender.",
    "Stir in the cooked bacon and chopped parsley.",
    "Serve hot, garnished with additional parsley if desired."
